nt color=#333333>(11/7/00 6:39:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~crodley/Ascii/wave.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1>   Hi folks, <br>
<br>
  I'll probably hit level 39 this weekend (gotta love those Golras!) and I'm wondering where would be a good place to &quot;Bottom Feed?&quot;<br>
 <br>
In other words, what are the best creatures that I could let my pet solo for no exp that have the best loot?<br>
<br>
Of course, I won't be a pest for the people hunting those for exp, I'll play nice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ascii<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureaperrp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ReaperRP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/00 8:51:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Best consistent loot that I've seen are sisters in OOT. I made so much more money fighting there then anywhere else. 2 of the sisters (one in the little hut named Ascania Halfbin, and one in the big hut with the merchant forgot her name), carry A longswords, which sells to the merchant for 11p, + a 1p belt + some change +occasional words/runes/pages.<br>
<br>
6 min spawn, it was great loot and exp from 30-34, and should be fast loot at 39. Whip out a fire pet and kill everything. MAKE ABSOLUTELY SURE you don't aggro the sister in the other little though. Hits for over 300, and you don't wanna mess with her. <p><html>
<img src="http://www.magecompendium.com/Images/Reaper.gif" height="135" width="90" >
<centre><b>Renesh, Level 40 Magician <br>
Reneshen Daemonsbane, Level 32 Paladin <br>
Reneshenn, Level 20 Rogue <br>

</b>
</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utejaye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tejaye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/00 9:03:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   OOT</span><hr size=1> Will I become KOS anywhere if I kill the Sisters?<br>
Also...be careful of that Level 60 Warrior npc (Styria Fearnon). She sometimes wanders and will kill you quickly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utvenya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tvenya</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/00 4:26:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Sisters in OOT</span><hr size=1> Yes, you will become to woodelfs everywhere if you kill them.  Also a warning.  Styria Fearnon used to be level 40-42ish.  She isn't anymore as she con'd red to me at 51.  Don't get anywhere near her if you are KOS, as she will kill you in a couple of seconds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utvenya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tvenya</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/00 4:27:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   BAH</span><hr size=1> Bad Tvenya.  Sorry, I didn't proof read obviously.  Last post was meant to say, you WILL become KOS by killing the sisters in OOT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/00 7:22:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sisters in OOT</span><hr size=1> Styria is a warrior guildmaster, and I believe that all guildmasters are by definition level 60. They also quad hit in the 300's. Definite ouchie.<br>
<br>
Druids are also pretty good loot. My wife is an evil necro and I've watched her killing treants and druids for easy experience and mondo loot and just sighed in jealousy. This weekend I took the plunge and killed a few myself, but I've still got dubious faction with them. Did the same thing with the dwarves... hunted them down to dubious. I haven't turned to the dark side yet, but I'm definately tainted. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
The druids in WC drop plenty of ringmail, fine steel (sometimes two) and longbows which are worth 2pp. And you can sell it to the merchant right there, who seems to be indifferent to everybody. There's two of them, and they respawn every six minutes. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 35th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A> at: 11/7/00 1:27:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureaperrp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ReaperRP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/00 5:49:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sisters in OOT</span><hr size=1> Ok, by killing sisters you do lose faction with quite a lot of places, but there is a VERY VERY easy quest to get it back. Kill as many sisters as you want, but watch until your faction hits dubious (takes a while, faction hits are small. Make sure you don't drop below dubious. When you're at dubious, run/gate/port over to Freeport, and go the West(or was it East? The one without the docks and without the bank). Anyway, once there go to the Brownloe Bakery, and buy as many muffins as you can hold, then walk over to the HogCallers Inn, go upstairs and talk to the dwarf. Hand them in in 4 stacks of 4 at a time, and within 15 mins your faction will be as good, or better, than it was before with all the places you lost it with killing sisters. <p><html>
<img src="http://www.magecompendium.com/Images/Reaper.gif" height="135" width="90" >
<centre><b>Renesh, Level 40 Magician <br>
Reneshen Daemonsbane, Level 32 Paladin <br>
Reneshenn, Level 20 Rogue <br>

</b>
</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uascii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/00 6:45:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~crodley/Ascii/wave.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1>   Thanks for the suggestion folks, but I think I should have been more specific.<br>
  <br>
I'd like to take no faction hits with any races (not including mobs of course) and I'd really like to avoid places that are usually camped.  I've never gone to the sister island without seeing somebody camping them.<br>
<br>
I suppose I'm wondering which all around general wandering type of mob, say around level 30 that carries the best loot.<br>
<br>
And now I find myself stuck with about 3 bubbles left to hit level 39.  I was on the Golra Iceberg, but all the Hulking Golras turned into Halara's which are yellow to me at 38, and since the Hulking Golra's nearly kill me, I'm definitely not going to try the Halara. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  <br>
So now on that cold, floating Gilligan's Island I'm scratching my head at the Halara's which I can't touch, and the regular Golra's which are green and no longer give exp.<br>
<br>
Ahh well, time to go explore the rest of Level 38 Norrath I guess <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ascii <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/00 8:01:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Good loot + Zero faction hit + not camped is going to be one tough combo to find. People have a tendency to flock to those kind of camps.<br>
<br>
You might try bouncers in Feerott. Unless you're a DE, I don't imagine ogre faction matters to you. I've never camped these, so I can't give much advice about it. I checked the bridge the other day, and got Bouncer Flerb alone. He conned yellow to me at 35, so I zoned him, but I imagine you could solo him. Guards respawn every six minutes, so this might be a good camp for you.<br>
<br>
Also might try the single spectre spawn in that zone. He's often camped, but if he's open then you could solo him, with fair loot. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 35th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufaang243.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faang243</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/00 8:36:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://cascarbre.tripod.com/faang2.jpg width=120 height=195></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> From a monk perspective, SOLA is where its at.<br>
<br>
Those gobbies carry ALOT of FS, plus the drops you can get at 40 sell for pretty good..<br>
<br>
To top it off, theres a gnome vendor you can sell to right inside the dungeon =)<br>
<br>
No Racial hits, (Unless you kill gnomes), Vendor in zone, and TONS of FS =)<br>
<br>
Very nice place for your level, you and your pet can clean up =) <p>Fanng Swiftscale
34th Level Iksar Monkey</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uascii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/00 4:31:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~crodley/Ascii/wave.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Good ideas, thanks all...I just finished doing my last Focus Item (hence my empty pocketbook) so since I'm right there I'll try the Sol A thing.<br>
<br>
Thanks again folks.<br>
<br>
Ascii <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureaperrp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ReaperRP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/00 6:19:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Hmm... Almost everytime I went to Sister Island, it was uncamped.... Guess it varies between servers.<br>
<br>
 <p><html>
<img src="http://www.magecompendium.com/Images/Reaper.gif" height="135" width="90" >
<centre><b>Renesh, Level 40 Magician <br>
Reneshen Daemonsbane, Level 32 Paladin <br>
Reneshenn, Level 20 Rogue <br>

</b>
</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/00 7:17:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> See my writeup on camping Kindle in the 29-34 section of this board. At 39-40 I don't imagine there's much experience for you in Sol A. Inferno gobs, Solusek gobs, and some gnomes will probably be the only blue cons to you. If you just need money, however, then you can go through and mow down any goblin that's cinder grade or higher. They DO drop a ton of FS, and also bricks of High quality ore. The small bricks sell for 2pp, the large ones sell for 8pp.<br>
<br>
I spent all of levels 29 to 34 camping Kindle. Sol A is one of my favorite dungeons. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 35th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> magin</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/10/00 9:07:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   post 39 kills</span><hr size=1> I have a level 54 mage.  I suggest you go to the giant camp near Firona.  You will not be able to take the verdan, but you can certainly solo an arbor.  The forest giants drop tunics, either items, some plat and rarely the forest loop.  The experience is great and  the plat is good.  There are three static spawns,  Set up your pet at the back of the camp on the hill next to the zone.  Find the tree which lines up with two of the giants.  Set up your pet just in front of that tree.  You can pull the giant (solo) to the right of the huts and back around to your pet.  Use any type of pull,  DD or malaise.  The two lined up on the left do not follow it to the right.  I use the earth pet with a damage shield.  Nuke hard and be prepare to move around a little if they come off the pet.  Here is how to take the left two.  Stand just before that tree which lines up with both of them with your back to the hill.  Use a low level bolt.  The bolt should reach the first one and pull it only.  If you use a dd or malaise they both come.  Rarely willl both come if you bolt the first one.  If two come send in the pet and gate home.  The second one on the left can be pulled afterward.  Make sure the other two have not spawned.  These giants spawn every six minutes.  As a 39 you will only be able to keep up on one.  Take the giant on the right.  At 44 you can keep up with two spawns by yourself.   At 49 you can own the camp, but arbors dont give ex normally and it gets boring.  Watch the verdans.  They should be avoided at 39.  This is a great place for a small group. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Xoran</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/10/00 9:30:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Warslik woods</span><hr size=1> Hrm I am not sure of the feasiblity of this but I would suggest one possibility is trying out warsliks woods and doing the grachnist camp.  Grachnist is a level 35ish goblin who is a fairly hard fight I would imagine at your level, probably like dwarf NPCs in butcher.  However this camp is usually fairly easy since he can spawn in any spawn point that a goblin spawns in and they are lower level.  So you just camp a set of spawns and hope he spawns.  You can get a standard item iksar gloves which are worth about 200pp, as well an occasional rare (1 in 30) of a totem of warrior spirit or shrunken golbin skull earring both of which are worth 3kpp or more.<br>
<br>
I'd ask around somemore though on this since I didn't do the camp until well into my 50s, but I think you could probably pull it off at 39.<br>
<br>
Xoran<br>
Magi, 57, Povar<br>
