Go to wisp isle and go crazy on those wisps with your 39 fire...or air, or earth, or water. It hardly matters. Heck, even whip out Monster Summoning 1, and you'll do fine. Heh, get a wisp pet. That's funny.<br>
Anyway, take the GLS's (that's Greater Lightstones) to the North K (I think it's north K...could be wrong about that) and go to the gypsy camp. There is an NPC named Mrysila there. Hand her the lightstones, and she will give you a Concordance of Research, which is used in Enchanter/Mage/Wizard/Necro practice research. Take the Concordance of Research and sell it back to her for 8pp. (NOTE: the Concordance of Research is a container, so you'll have to give her one or two greater lightstones and then sell. Boring, but that's the way it is)<br>
<br>
This is a VERY easy way to make cash. Boring as hell, but it works <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Balthemal says: "Save me, Jboots, save me!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=polonius>Polonius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(7/7/01 9:45:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Here are 2 suggestions that no one seems to remember. <br>
First: If you just want some quick cash, you can go to Everfrost and hunt mother mammoths. They drop tusks that are sellable to barbarian vendors for 7-10pp each(depending on your charisma). With your dimensional holes you can carry a ton of them at once. You can solo them easily with a fire pet. They almost always drop 1 tusk and frequently drop 2.<br>
<br>
Second: You can camp Cynthia at the gypsy camp near the Lake Rathe zone in Rathe Mountains. She is a lv 30 wizzy mob. She will cast magic, fire, and ice based spells against you but she only has 600 hp. You can solo her easily with an earth pet and about 2 cinder bolts per spawn(at least pre-aggro nerf, hehe). You will take no faction hits and none of the other gypsies in the camp will help her. She is a regular 5 min spawn and drops loot up to about 4pp plus the odd gem, jewelry(normal not enchanted), or words. She can easily take you to lvl 41 and I still get xp from her at that lvl(but not much).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udeenor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deenor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(7/7/01 7:30:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Man, you are SO overlooking the BEST camp until 45.  Three words:   THE GREAT OOWOMP!<br>
<br>
He's got some highly respectable loot and awesome exp.  He's lvl 34 and can kick the butt of any non-caster under lvl 40, but I was soloing him at 35 with an earth pet.  Had only a couple of problems, but if you're bound to the docks in Oasis, you can get back quickly.<br>
<br>
Just keep in mind that he SoW's himself INSTANTLY upon spawning.  Keep your pet FAST and be ready to run if you accidentally pull the other ogres.  They don't hit hard, but they bash a LOT.<br>
<br>
Here's the exact method I used to take him:<br>
1) Use earth pet and have him burned out and fire shielded<br>
2) Pull with malise so pet can root and your nukes stick<br>
3) After about 10 seconds of Pet/Oowomp combat, use RAIN on him.  (yep your RAIN line of spells don't break your pet's root)<br>
4) If all 3 of the RAIN waves hit, you can probably sit back.  I usually did it twice to make sure I KS'd the pet and pet had fall back HP incase something else aggro'd.<br>
5) Oowomp will turn to run when he's low.  If the pet can NOT keep him rooted, you MUST send a nuke and FAST.  Shortly after he starts to run, he'll usually stop and quickly GATE to his spawn point.  At this point in the fight he does a fast heal or worse (two or three).  If you're VERY unlucky, he'll get 3 heals off while your pet is heading back from the waters edge.  Now, Oowomp's headed back to finish the job and may bring his lvl 18 to 20ish ogre friend from inside the house.  As you can see, this is where things get bad.<br>
<br>
So, to avoid number 5, have SHOCK OF xxxxx up and ready to go.<br>
<br>
Oh, don't try to solo Oowomp till 35.  If you can't med and watch the activity, you'll spend all your exp on corpse runs.  Basically, if you try to camp Oowomp at 34 and med as needed, you'll soon be 33. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=polonius>Polonius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(7/8/01 6:47:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions for good Loot kills?</span><hr size=1> Regarding Deenor's post about the great Oowomp. Excellent idea Deenor, I'd forgotten about Oowomp. I don't find that he gives me much xp but I was 40(hell lvl) when I last camped him. Yes his loot is respectable, especially if you have a wisdom based caster that your equipping. Just keep in mind that he will dot you with scourge, which hits for 400 in several ticks(not sure how many). I have been hit with scourge, finished killing Oowomp, then start bandaging myself and survived it. Of course I keep phantom chain up while I'm camping him. I found that cinder bolt works better for me instead of a rain spell because he seems to break root fairly easily. Also, if he manages to gate, the bolt will still follow him and singe his tail. I also usually pull with cinder bolt, which will unfortunately get a lot of his attention before pet can taunt him off, but lets you get in a hefty initial amount of damage from the get go. Just my 2cp worth, hope it helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showMessageRange?topicID=96.topic&s